			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I'm usually the most unlucky guy in the world when it comes to EQ but tonight was a different story. About 2 hours ago I came here to find out where to get both Cornacopia and Everfont and left not feeling too confident of success. My first stop was Freeport where, while stopping by the bank, went into a shop and just happened to find 1 Words of Trancendence. Then it was off to Qeynos where, in the Magician's Guild I found Cornacopia and Level 1 Summon water. I don't remember clearly what my research score is but it says &quot;Very Bad&quot;. I scribed Cornacopia and put the Words, level 1 spell and a globe of non-summoned water into my Elemental Binder and POOF! Worked on the first shot. I don't know why so many people are having such a hard time with this...all I can think of is they probably didn't do any practicing on thier research. <BR>

				</font>
